{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, systematically mapping combinations of network attributes and dynamical regimes to a range of computational functions could assist the design of ad hoc or problem-specific tailored architectures.",
    "Due to their physical nature, neuromorphic systems are limited by spatial, material and energetic constraints, akin to biological neural networks.",
    "Because of this, insights gained about the economical organization of brain networks could contribute to the cost-effective design of these information-processing systems 35.",
    "Furthermore, the fact that training only occurs at the readout stage makes RC an extraordinarily computationally efficient learning approach.",
    "In addition to this, parallel information processing can be achieved by simultaneously training multiple readout modules to perform various parallel tasks."
  ]
}